title: The Americas
subTitle: Mexico, where deserts meet tropics; see new footage of fledgling pygmy owls, orca hunting, new species in flooded caves and orchid bees filmed in incredible detail -- all revealing the hidden lives of unique wildlife.

title: Predator Countdown
subTitle: A look at the diverse continent of South America, where a pod of killer whales snatch baby seals right under their mothers' noses, and a jaguar hunts caimans in the jungle.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Parenthood
subTitle: Parenting in the ocean demands dedication and intelligence. From navigating the reef, to teaching young to hunt giants, these parents have remarkable strategies.

title: Italy: The Last Wilderness Year 1
subTitle: Surviving the vast mountains of Italy, the chamois are an endemic group of species that are facing a series threat of extinction.

title: The Lions Rule
subTitle: A nasty cub attempts to mate with members of the pride, and is immediately, violently, asked to leave the group by an authoritative adult in the pride.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: A fragile strip of tropical woodland that extends along the east coast of Australia. It is a place of refuge for fauna, including birds of paradise and cassowaries.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: In north Tanzania, towering mountains line a dramatic valley. Enriched by ancient volcanoes, its slopes provide a variety of habitats for life to thrive and its great centerpiece holds water through even the driest of times.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: In the Kruger National Park in South Africa, Dianne finds a boomslang and a chameleon in a duel on the tar road. Not a environment where they would encounter each other under any normal circumstances.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: Spanish juniper woods are some of the most characterful in the world. Each juniper tree has its own shape, and the woodlands are adapted to cold and dry climates.

subTitle: Explores the mechanics of camouflage used by creatures like octopuses and chameleons for disguising themselves in the wild.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: Table Mountain National Park on the southwestern tip of Africa surrounded by ocean and humanity. It is a rugged peninsula jutting out into the cold Atlantic Ocean and forming an island of incredible diversity.

title: Wild Fighters
subTitle: Investigating the different reasons that lead animals to face tough disputes.

title: Okavango: River of Dreams
subTitle: The extraordinary landscape and wildlife of the middle world of the Okavango River in Southern Africa.

title: Zambia Untamed
subTitle: The plains and woodlands of the Luangwa Valley are the wildest and most merciless of all neighbourhoods where duels between predator and prey are played out both day and night. For the animals that call this home, it's a daily battle to stay alive.

title: New Kids in the Wild
subTitle: In South Africa's Greater Kruger Park, lion cub Chiga has been born into a family of hunters, and now she must find her place in the pride.

title: Chasing the Rains
subTitle: The elephants dig wells as the rain suddenly pours; a group of lions kill one of cheetah Kuleta's cubs; wild dog Phoenix fights off a pack of hyena.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: There are many fine examples of evolutionary history in the natural world. Animals adapt through a series of small, random mutations and usually do so in order to compete more effectively for food, water and space. Crocodiles are certainly of an ancient lineage, they are believed to be 200 million years old. Sharks have gone through the process of adaptation and evolutionary experimentation as well.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Beautiful but deadly, these cats rule the animal kingdom. Follow the plight of four species as they struggle to survive in four very different landscapes.

title: The Americas
